Note:
Runa Standard Library: Async Streams Module

Provides reactive stream processing capabilities with backpressure handling,
stream transformations, and enterprise-grade streaming patterns.

Features:
- Reactive streams with backpressure
- Stream transformations and operators
- Stream fusion and optimization
- Error handling and recovery
- Memory-efficient streaming
:End Note

Import "async.async" as async
Import "async.queue" as queue

Note: Stream Types
Type AsyncStream is Dictionary with:
    stream_id as String
    source as Optional[Process]
    transformations as List[Process]
    subscribers as List[Process]
    buffer_size as Integer
    closed as Boolean
    error_handler as Optional[Process]

Type StreamOperator is:
    | MAP with transform as Process
    | FILTER with predicate as Process
    | REDUCE with accumulator as Process
    | TAKE with count as Integer
    | SKIP with count as Integer

Note: Stream Creation
Process called "create_stream" that takes source as Optional[Process] and buffer_size as Integer returns AsyncStream:
    Return AsyncStream with:
        stream_id as generate_unique_id
        source as source
        transformations as list containing
        subscribers as list containing
        buffer_size as buffer_size
        closed as false
        error_handler as None

Async Process called "from_iterable" that takes items as List[Any] returns AsyncStream:
    Let stream be create_stream with source as None and buffer_size as 100
    
    For each item in items:
        Await emit with stream as stream and item as item
    
    close_stream with stream as stream
    Return stream

Process called "map_stream" that takes stream as AsyncStream and transform as Process returns AsyncStream:
    Add MAP with transform as transform to stream["transformations"]
    Return stream

Process called "filter_stream" that takes stream as AsyncStream and predicate as Process returns AsyncStream:
    Add FILTER with predicate as predicate to stream["transformations"]
    Return stream

Async Process called "collect_stream" that takes stream as AsyncStream returns List[Any]:
    Let results be list containing
    
    Async For each item in stream:
        Add item to results
    
    Return results

Note: Stream Processing
Async Process called "emit" that takes stream as AsyncStream and item as Any returns None:
    If stream["closed"]:
        Return
    
    Note: Apply transformations
    Let processed_item be item
    For each transformation in stream["transformations"]:
        Match transformation:
            When MAP with transform as transform:
                Set processed_item to transform with item as processed_item
            When FILTER with predicate as predicate:
                If not predicate with item as processed_item:
                    Return  Note: Item filtered out
    
    Note: Send to subscribers
    For each subscriber in stream["subscribers"]:
        Await subscriber with item as processed_item

Process called "subscribe" that takes stream as AsyncStream and subscriber as Process returns None:
    Add subscriber to stream["subscribers"]

Process called "close_stream" that takes stream as AsyncStream returns None:
    Set stream["closed"] to true